# The toolchain this project is built and shipped with. asdf and mise both read this, so
# entering the directory is enough to be on it.
#
# It exists because the versions had drifted apart: development was on OTP 29, CI on 28,
# and the release binaries were compiled with Elixir 1.18 while the container image used
# 1.20.2. One tag was shipping artifacts out of two different compilers, and nothing
# compared them.
#
# OTP is held at 28 deliberately. 29 is out, but Burrito (which packages the binaries
# people download) cannot build against it: the release fails in Zig's link step and
# produces nothing. Raise this when Burrito supports 29, together with
# .github/workflows/{ci,release}.yml and the Dockerfile's ARGs, which say the same thing.
erlang 28.5.0.3
elixir 1.20.2-otp-28
